oups(request_id, owner_group, group_order)`\n- `workflow_request_risk_signals(request_id, signal_name, detail, signal_order)`\n- **Output/scalar tables** (these are the write targets, defined as single `value text` columns but used in JS as arrays of objects): `workflow_state`, `owner_tasks`, `audit_events`, `customer_messages`.\n\n### 5. Test File (CRITICAL — full contents)\n`tests/acceptance.test.mjs` — imports `applyBenchmarkTask` from workflow.mjs and `buildPortalView` from portal-view.mjs. Full contents already pasted above. Key assertions the implementation must satisfy:\n\n**Before state** (from `buildPortalView` on raw data): status `\"Needs work\"`, history `\"Not visible\"`, tasks `\"0 owner tasks\"`.\n\n**After `applyBenchmarkTask(runData, now)`** where `now = \"2026-06-18T12:00:00.000Z\"`:\n- `after.status` === `\"At-risk escalation active with executive recovery owner routing and customer-visible audit history.\"`\n- `after.owner` === owner_groups sorted by `group_order`, mapped to `owner_group`, joined with `\" + \"` → `\"Customer Success + Support + Finance + Executive Sponsor\"`\n- `after.nextStep.length > 8`\n- `after.history` === `\"Audit visible\"`\n- `after.customerMessage.length > 12`\n- `after.riskSummary` === `` `${n} signals: ${names.join(\", \")}` `` → `\"6 signals: strategic, account, rescue, enterprise account, open customer impact, audit required\"`\n- `after.tasks` === `\"4 owner tasks\"`\n\n**Persisted-state assertions** (`assertPersistedState` on `runData` — the workflow MUST mutate the passed-in tables):\n- `workflow_state` has a row with `request_id === request.request_id` and `status === expectedStatus`.\n- `owner_tasks`: one row per owner group, `owner_group` values in sorted order, and **every** task has truthy `title`, truthy `due_at`, and `status === \"open\"`.\n- `customer_messages`: a row with matching `request_id` and truthy `body`.\n- `audit_events`: a row with matching `request_id` and truthy `customer_visible`.\n\n### 6. M